This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with depth completion using RGB and depth information. It also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on indoor and outdoor scenes, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of canonical correlation analysis as a training objective suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
